<DOCNO> XIE19990822.0002 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Formulates Food Security Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia has formulated a
program aimed at improving the country's food security, Ethiopian
News Agency reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The program is deemed to enable Ethiopia to become
self-sufficient in food, Niway Gebre-Ab, economic advisor in the
office of Prime Minister Meles Zanawi, was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
By making the program, the government is exerting efforts to
minimize the number of people in the rural areas being affected by
shortage of food, Niway said.
</P>
<P>
A food crisis occurred in Ethiopia since March this year which
witnessed drought in many parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
Some 4.6 million people have been affected in this Horn of
Africa country, an official statistics said.
</P>
<P>
A number of countries and world organizations have made
donations to Ethiopia in the past few months.
</P>
<P>
Although the world community has been offering food aid for
years, Ethiopia, with a population of 60 million and depending on
natural harvest, has never escaped from food shortage.
</P>
<P>
According to Niway, about two million people in the rural areas
need relief food even when there is regular rainfall.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopian acting Agriculture Minister Mengistu Huluka Friday
appealed to the people of the whole country to exert efforts to
tackle the problems of food shortage and drought.
</P>
<P>
In addition to farmers, private entrepreneurs have also been
urged to play a significant role in developing the agricultural
sector of the national economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
