<HEADLINE> UAE, US Hold Joint Military Exercise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Forces from the United Arab
Emirates (UAE) and the United States are holding a joint military
exercise in UAE waters.
</P>
<P>
Personnel from the UAE air, navy and special forces are
participating in the war games, which started late Friday, the
official WAM news agency reported on Saturday, without mentioning
the scale of the U.S. participation.
</P>
<P>
The aim of the exercise, code-named Iron Magic 99, is to
enhance the military cooperation between the UAE and the U.S. and
boost the combat readiness of the UAE forces within its borders,
WAM added.
</P>
<P>
It noted that the exercise was part of a series of joint
training being conducted by the UAE armed forces with "friendly
forces," which obviously referring to U.S., British and French
forces that help the Gulf country improve its military equipment
and combat capability.
</P>
<P>
The UAE is especially concerned about its powerful neighbor
Iran, with which it has a dispute over three strategically
important Gulf islands.
</P>
<P>
The three islands, Abu Musa, Greater Tunb and Lesser Tunb, are
claimed by both countries but being occupied by Iran.
</P>
<P>
The UAE accuses Iran of being reluctant to respond to its
calls for a peaceful solution to the dispute through dialogs or
international arbitration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
