<HEADLINE> Liberia Asks U.N. to Provide Emergency Help to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Liberian Government said Saturday
that the country does not have the means to cope with the
worsening refugee flood issue from the fighting areas between
government troops and rebels and appealed to the international
community for help.
</P>
<P>
Liberian Information Minister Joe Mulbah said that the United
Nations should give his country urgent food and medical aid to
help tide off the worsening humanitarian emergency in the northern
part of the country, according to reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
Mulbah said towns in the fighting areas along the
Liberian-Guinean border towns were being burnt in "rampant acts
of arson" -- with thousands of civilians caught in the cross
fire, and an unknown number killed.
</P>
<P>
He said government forces were exerting "all efforts to stop
civilian casualties".
</P>
<P>
The United Nations High Commission for Refugees (UNHCR), which
says it hopes to be able to return to the area soon, pulled its
staff out of the region last week because of the security
situation and the taking of hostages by rebels.
</P>
<P>
A World Food Program official indicated today in Monrovia that
international aid organizations might not be able to provide
immediate relief to the remote-fighting region. Earlier this
week the government announced the capture of the towns of Foya,
Kolahun and Medekoma. But the government troops' further offensive
is believed to be difficult.
</P>
<P>
The fighting began last week when armed insurgents crossed into
Lofa County from neighboring Guinea. Liberian Government had
declared a state of emergency in the area and accused Guinea of
providing support for the rebels.
</P>
<P>
Guinean President Lansana Conte latter denied Liberia's charge
and accused the Liberian authorities of ingratitude toward his
country.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on Africa No 1 radio, Conte said, "Guinea continues to
give assistance and to harbor thousands of Liberian refugees."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
