<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-21 17:34 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 19 Killed in Floods in Northern Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Floods triggered by torrential
rains have hit Iran's northern province of Gazvin, killing 19
people and leaving six others missing.
</P>
<P>
A local official said Saturday that heavy rainfall caused
overflow of three main rivers in the area, setting off the floods
which inflicted severe damages in 17 villages throughout the
province Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
He was quoted by the official Islamic Republic News Agency as
saying that electricity and telephone lines have been cut off in
eight villages as a result of the floods.
</P>
<P>
Major roads in eight provincial villages have also been
damaged whereas rural roads, drinking water networks, agricultural
installations and over 150 hectares of farmlands and orchards
were severely affected, he said.
</P>
<P>
Relief teams have rushed to the flood-stricken areas to
distribute aid to the victims, help find those missing and to
clear up the roads, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
