<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Palestinian Faction Leader in Cairo for Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The leader of an major
Palestinian opposition group arrived in Cairo on Saturday for a
meeting with Palestine Liberation Organization (PLO) Chairman
Yasser Arafat.
</P>
<P>
Nayef Hawatmeh, secretary general of the Democratic Front for
the Liberation of Palestine (DFLP), is to lead his group's
delegation to the meeting with that of Fatah, led by Arafat, on
Sunday, Egypt's Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
This will be the first meeting between the two men and also the
two groups since the 1993 signing of the Oslo accord between the
PLO and Israel, which forms the basis of the two sides' peace
talks.
</P>
<P>
Fatah, PLO's most powerful faction, is the major force to
support the Oslo accord while the Damascus-based DFLP, PLO's third
largest group, opposes the peace agreement and the peace talks
with Israel.
</P>
<P>
The planned meeting, which was initially scheduled for August
11, is aimed at reaching a national reconciliation among the
Palestinian groups and forming a united Palestinian position on
the final status talks between the Palestinians and Israel.
</P>
<P>
In an earlier effort to mend fences with other Palestinian
factions, Arafat met with a delegation of the People's Front for
the Liberation of Palestine (PFLP). The two sides agreeed to
further hold dialog and expressed hope that the other Palestinian
factions will join the reconciliation process.
</P>
<P>
PFLP, another radical group also based in Damascus, Syria, is
opposed to the Oslo accord, too. 
</P>
</TEXT>
