<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 25 Injured in Countrywide Strike in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- At least 25 people were injured,
with one seriously, in the dawn-to-dusk nationwide hartal
(destructive strike) called by the opposition alliance in
Bangladesh on Sunday, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said a man was seen hurling a bomb at a passenger bus
in the capital city injuring at least 11 of the passengers,
including four women, and the man was caught on the spot and
handed over to police.
</P>
<P>
One of the passengers was seriously injured and rushed to a
nearby hospital. Some 41 persons were arrested for allegedly
involving in violence.
</P>
<P>
A report from southwestern Khulna district said police and
hartal activists clashed there Sunday evening, but no injuries
were reported.
</P>
<P>
The opposition alliance, comprising the Bangladesh Nationalist
Party (BNP), the Jatiya Party, the Jamaat-e-Islami and the Islamic
Oikya Jote, enforced the 12-hour shutdown to protest against the
killing of one of its activists and police action on
demonstrations during the gherao of district deputy commissioners'
offices across the country last Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The strike, which was originally set for six hours but extended
to 12 hours on Friday, was imposed as part of the opposition's
movement to resist the government' move to allow transshipment
facilities to India.
</P>
<P>
The four parties brought out torch processions and held rallies
in the capital Saturday to drum up public support for the hartal.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the BSS news agency said the ruling Bangladesh Awami
League and its front organizations brought out "peace processions"
in the capital streets protesting the countrywide hartal.
</P>
<P>
The Daily Star reported that more than 5,000 riot police,
battalion police and members of the paramilitary Bangladesh Rifles
were deployed at strategic points and important establishments in
the city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
