<HEADLINE> Over 1,000 Kilograms of Drugs Seized in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 22 (Xinhua) -- More than 1,000 kilograms of
drugs have been seized by Iran's Law Enforcement Forces near
the capital and in the southern province of Kerman, according
to reports reaching here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The reports said 167 kilograms of drugs were seized in
Karaj, a satellite city of Tehran, on Saturday from a gang
of drug traffickers.
</P>
<P>
Five members of the gang were involved in trafficking narcotics
from Kerman province to the west of Tehran, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
During the fifth month (July 21-August 22) of the current
Iranian year, 93 drug traffickers were arrested in the west of
Tehran province and some 491 kilograms of drugs were seized.
</P>
<P>
Over 927 kilograms of drugs were seized in "stop and
search operations" in Kerman province from a lorry carrying
construction material. In this connection one man was arrested
and the vehicle confiscated.
</P>
<P>
The drug haul included opium, morphine and hashish.
</P>
<P>
Iran has been a transit route for drug trafficking from
Pakistan and Afghanistan to Europe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
