<HEADLINE> Brazil Wins Manila Leg of Women's Volley GP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The third straight win in Manila brought the Brazilians, who
finished the four-leg preliminaries with 12 points, the title and
the 60,000 U.S. dollars top purse.
</P>
<P>
Brazil will join Italy, Russia and China in the crossover semi-
finals August 28-29 in China, where a 370,000 dollars pot topped
by a 200,000 dollars champion's prize is on offer.
</P>
<P>
Starting the first set poorly 26-28, the Brazilian came back
strongly in the three following sets and won 25-17, 25-21, 25-23
over the Cubans, also Olympic champions from the Atlanta Games.
</P>
<P>
Spikers Virna Dias and Janina Conceicao spearheaded the Brazil'
s offensives to eliminate the formidable Cubans in the contention.
</P>
<P>
Brazil, seeking the fourth Grand Prix title, showed its full
force at the start of second set for a 25-17 win.
</P>
<P>
They were able to sustain their fiery attack, despite the
Cubans' determined efforts.
</P>
<P>
Ace hitters Mckenzie Regla Bell and Yumilka Ruiz took charge of
the Cubans' attack until the end.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilians, however, never gave up with Dias who went for a
kill in the last set.
</P>
<P>
In the three-day Manila leg of the GP, Cuba ranked second by
beating South Korean and Italy while Italy ranked third by
defeating South Korea. The South Koreans lost all its three
matches here. 
</P>
</TEXT>
