<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S'pore PM Stresses "Honesty, Efficiency" in Globalization Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Prime Minister Goh
Chok Tong Sunday emphasized the importance of keeping "honesty and
efficiency" in the city-state's economic globalization process.
</P>
<P>
Goh said in a speech delivered at the Nation Day Rally here
that "honesty and efficiency are two values that have helped
Singapore to overcome the economic crisis."
</P>
<P>
With the help of the two values, the Singapore economy, unlike
others in the region, has not been harmed by the crisis and is
recovering with healthy growth in the first half of 1999, Goh
said.
</P>
<P>
He said that in the next stage of development, Singapore must
globalize its economy and "make the quantum leap from being a
regional economy to become one of the few global centers of
excellence."
</P>
<P>
As a resource-poor country, said Goh, Singapore must depend on
intangible assets, that is, honesty and efficiency.
</P>
<P>
"If we lose these great assets, foreign investors will lose
confidence in us. Singapore will be finished," Goh cautioned.
</P>
<P>
He said that instead of relying solely on buying and selling
other people's products to make a living, Singapore have to look
for new opportunities and adjust its strategies in tandem with
changes in the environment.
</P>
<P>
"This is time for us to go global, competing head on with the
developed economies," he said.
</P>
<P>
He also urged Singapore companies to have products which can
sell in the world market so as to "build a first-world economy and
a world-class home." 
</P>
</TEXT>
