<HEADLINE> People's Daily Says People Should Learn A Lesson From Falun Gong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- China's leading newspaper "
People's Daily" carries an article in Monday's edition that says
the Chinese should learn a lesson from the struggle against Falun
Gong and that the effort to expose Li Hongzhi, its founder, has
achieved a great deal.
</P>
<P>
People also need to ponder why so many people were deceived by
the Falun Gong cult, it says, even though it was against science,
human beings, society, and government.
</P>
<P>
The article says that cadres and Communist Party members should
improve their political sense and political study and that the
fight against Falun Gong has an important bearing on the
fundamental faith of communists, on the ideological basis for
uniting the Chinese people, and on the destiny and future of the
Communist Party and the government.
</P>
<P>
Party members need to increase their Marxist study, with
emphasis on materialism and atheism, which are powerful weapons in
defeating the enemy, it says, as well as develop a scientific
spirit and fight against superstition and to be vigilant.
</P>
<P>
The Communist Party of China is the ruling party with over 61
million members and it has many advantages that include theory,
organization, and policy, it says.
</P>
<P>
It is also very important to rule the country by law and to
improve social management, which will improve people's legal sense,
it says. Many Falun Gong practitioners have the desire to improve
their health but didn't clearly understand the nature of Li
Hongzhi and his anti-government goals so more attention should be
paid to people's need for health and entertainment.
</P>
<P>
The article concludes by saying that no one can stop the great
undertaking because people have matured after the struggle with
Falun Gong and have united around the CPC with Jiang Zemin at its
core and are insisting on the Party's basic line. 
</P>
</TEXT>
