<HEADLINE> Jet Catches Fire as Landing at Hong Kong Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 22 (Xinhua) -- A China Airlines jet caught
fire while landing at Hong Kong International Airport in a
tropical storm Sunday evening, killing two and injuring at least
212 of the 315 people on board, according to the Hong Kong
Hospital Authority.
</P>
<P>
The China Airlines MD-11 passenger plane carrying 315 people,
including 15 crew members, caught fire at 6:45 p.m. when it landed
at the airport amid a fierce storm.
</P>
<P>
The airliner, Flight CI-642, was flying from Bangkok to Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
Two passengers, who witnessed the accident, said that there was
no explosion on the plane, but a fire ball could be seen coming up.
</P>
<P>
Most of the passengers were Thais and Portuguese.  
</P>
