<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Postal Union Fighting Illegal Issuing of Stamps </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The Universal Postal Union (UPU)
has appointed a special task force recently to assist in combating
illegal postage stamps that are issued without authorization of
postal administrations.
</P>
<P>
According to a UPU news release at today's press conference for
the 22nd Universal Postal Congress (UPS), the sharp increase in
the number of illegal postage stamps issued without authorization
has caused deep concern among UPU member countries.
</P>
<P>
Thomas Leavey, director general of the UPU's International
Bureau, says that the problem is a serious one, especially for
developing countries that are losing revenues badly needed for
postal development.
</P>
<P>
These illegal activities mislead stamp collectors and tarnish
philately's image and it is time that the rules on issuing postage
stamps be re-examined, he said.
</P>
<P>
At a recent meeting of the UPU's World Association for the
Development of Philately, it was agreed that urgent action is
needed and a special task force was set up to develop a program
that will allow malefactors to be identified more easily and
information on illegal stamp issues to be exchanged more rapidly.
</P>
<P>
The 22nd Universal Postal Congress will open here on Monday.
Priority will be given to strengthening the UPU's Philately Code
of Ethics and to establishing sound philatelic strategies.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
