<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Relief Aid Needed: Turkish Officials </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Turkey's quake-stricken areas are
in need of more aid materials, Turkish officials said here on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The officials said the areas need tents, blankets, cleaning
and toilet materials, clothes, working machines to shift the
rubble, water tanks to store water and a 30-ton water tank for
the open-air hospital in Kocaeli province, about 110 kilometers
east of Istanbul.
</P>
<P>
The officials requested a total of 16 garbage trucks, 50,000
medical waste bags, mobile toilets and showers, tents and
blankets for the most seriously devastated provinces of Kocaeli
and Yalova.
</P>
<P>
Turkey's Interior Ministry issued a circular on Sunday,
calling on entertainment and shows in public entertainment places
to be reduced to the minumum.
</P>
<P>
The circular also requested the governors of Kocaeli, Sakarya
and Yalova to make the business vehicles to work for 24
hours.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Turkey's Bogazici University Kandilli Observatory
said two aftershocks measuring 4.0 on the Richter scale occurred
in Istanbul on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Over 60 aftershocks at least 4 on the Richter scale have
happened since the killer earthquake with a magnitude of 7.4 hit
the western Turkey on August 17. 
</P>
</TEXT>
