<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy Beats South Korea in Women's Volleyball GP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Italians won the match 13-25, 22-25, 26-24, 25-14, 15-10.
</P>
<P>
The South Koreans put up a solid defense to win the first two
sets but the Italians were more aggressive to take the third set.
</P>
<P>
While Italy continued to play well, South Korea suddenly lost
its composure, which allowed the Italians to control the fourth
and fifth set.
</P>
<P>
During the time-out, Italian coach Angiolino Frigoni told his
players to play with more intensity. The Italians responded well
and eventually won the next three sets with more co-ordinated
performance by Francesca Piccinini, Antonella Bragaglia, Simona
Gioli and Simona Rinieri.
</P>
<P>
Piccinini led the scorers with 24 points, including eight in
the fourth set where the Italians raced to an 12-2 lead before
taking the set 25-14.
</P>
<P>
Ku Min-Jung from South Korea was second with 20 points, who
posted a 10-9 lead in the fifth set before the Italians scored six
straight points to wrap up the match in one hour and 40 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Italy, South Korea, Cuba and Brazil are actually going for
crucial points that will get them entry into the crossover semi-
finals.
</P>
<P>
Competing in the other group in the Chinese Taipei leg are
Russia, Japan, China and the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
The GP finals will be staged in Yunnan province, China on
August 28-29. 
</P>
</TEXT>
