<HEADLINE> Photo Exhibition on Deng Xiaoping Held in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 22 (Xinhua) -- A five-day photo exhibition
featuring the ordinary family life of Deng Xiaoping, the chief
architect of China's reform and opening-up, was launched here on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is held as August 22 this year is the 95th
anniversary of Deng Xiaoping's birth. Deng died on February 29,
1997.
</P>
<P>
"This is not a historical photo exhibition, it is the indelible
memory of a daughter about her father," said Deng Lin, the eldest
daughter of Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Except several pictures which show Deng Lin's staying together
with her father, the rest of some 110 photos were shot by Deng Lin.
</P>
<P>
"I expect that the exhibition will enable Macao residents to
know more about the aspect of household life of my father," Deng
Lin said.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping put forward the concept of "one country, two
systems," which resolved the questions of Hong Kong and Macao.
Following Hong Kong's return to the motherland on July 1, 1997,
Macao's return will come on December 20 this year.
</P>
<P>
"It was a regret that my father was not able to go to Hong Kong
and Macao, so I think the exhibition may help fulfill his wish,"
Deng Lin said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
