<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Another Quake Occurs in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake occurred in
southeastern Turkey on Sunday afternoon, the semi-official
Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake with a preliminary magnitude of 4.3 struck
southeastern province of Elazig at 14:13 p.m local time (11:13
GMT), but no serious damage or injuries from the jolt were reported.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake was about 600 kilometers east of
Ankara, capital of Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The monster earthquake measuring 7.4 on the Richter scale hit
western Turkey in the early hours of August 17 and killed over
12,000 people and injured over 33,000 others in the region.
</P>
</TEXT>
