<HEADLINE> 2 Israeli Soldiers Wounded in South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Two Israeli soldiers were
wounded by mortar fire early Sunday in a buffer zone set up by
Israel in south Lebanon, Israel Radio said.
</P>
<P>
The radio said that one of them was hurt lightly, and another
suffered from medial injury.
</P>
<P>
The two soldiers were wounded at an army post in the eastern
sector of the buffer zone established by Israel in 1985 in south
Lebanon with a claimed aim of preventing its northern borders from
attacks by Lebanese guerrillas .
</P>
<P>
The report said that it was the Hezbollah group which launched
the attack.
</P>
<P>
Following the incident, Israeli troops returned cannon fire.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah has been the most active militant group in south
Lebanon fighting to oust Israeli troops from Lebanon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
