<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambian Artists Calls for Setting up Art School </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Zambian artists have urged the
government to set up an art school at any of the country's two
universities so that the development of art into an industry and
major tourist attractions can be accelerated.
</P>
<P>
A group of artists made the call when they met here Saturday to
discuss the forthcoming art exhibition to be held in the capital
later this month, according to Sunday Mail.
</P>
<P>
They said that art in Zambia has not been given the necessary
exposure to fully develop and encompass it as a major tourist
activity that can earn the country lots of money.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of an art school will encourage a lot of
people to fully develop their art skills and produce international
quality materials that will earn the country more money, they
said.
</P>
<P>
"We are getting into fourth decade of independence but we still
don't have an art school in university. We're probably the only
country in this part of the world that is denying the development
of creative thinking that goes with the teaching of art at higher
institutions of learning," an artist complained.
</P>
<P>
The art exhibition to be held is aimed at depicting the African
blend of culture as well as the technical aspect of the artists.
</P>
<P>
"We want to show the people that art is a profession like any
other form which you can earn a living," said the artist. 
</P>
</TEXT>
