<HEADLINE> Passenger Plane Caught Fire at Hong Kong Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 22 (Xinhua) -- One passenger was dead and
more than ten seriously injured as a passenger aircraft crashed at
the Hong Kong International Airport on Sunday evening according to
a local TV station.
</P>
<P>
The China Airlines MD-11 passenger plane carrying 315 people
caught fire at 6:45 p.m. when it landed at the Hong Kong
International Airport amid a fierce storm.
</P>
<P>
The airliner, Flight CI-642, was flying from Bangkok to Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
Two passengers, who witnessed the accident, said that there was
no explosion on the plane, but a fire ball could be seen coming up.
</P>
<P>
Most of the passengers were Thais and Portuguese. There was no
detailed report about how many people were injured.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft rushed out of runways and then turned over.
</P>
</TEXT>
