<TEXT>
<P>
The victory of the 17-year-old Melandri brought Honda a sweep
of the top three spots for the second consecutive event on the 125
cc circuit, following the teenager's first ever win at last month'
s German Grand Prix.
</P>
<P>
Melandri won in 41 minutes 23.897 seconds in the 102.65-km race,
followed by Japanese Noboru Ueda, who was 11.672 seconds behind
and Italian Lucio Cecchinello, 11.717 seconds behind Melandri.
</P>
