<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Industrial Competitiveness Increasing (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Editor's note: This year is the
50th anniversary of the People's Republic of China and, over the
past 50 years, China's achievements have attracted worldwide
attention, with comprehensive national strength increasing and
earth-shaking changes taking place in all sectors.
</P>
<P>
Xinhua News Agency will release about 20 reports on these
development and provide the latest information on the nation's
economy. The first of the series was released on August 17. This
is the third.
</P>
<P>
China's industrial economy was marked by small workshops 50
years ago, but has grown into a modern comprehensive industrial
system with increasing competitiveness, putting an end to the
shortages of manufactured goods.
</P>
<P>
The National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) reports that
manufacturing industry's total value added in 1998 amounted to
more than 2.6 trillion yuan, fourth in the world. China has also
ranked first in steel, coal, cement, chemical fertilizer, and TV
set production, since 1996.
</P>
<P>
The industrial sector has begun to cooperate with the rest of
the world as China's market-oriented reforms and opening up
continue. Manufactured goods have come to account for some 90
percent of the nation's total exports.
</P>
<P>
The steel industry, an important indicator of the national
economy and of comprehensive national strength, produced more than
100 million tons of steel in 1996 and has given backbone to
national economic development.
</P>
<P>
But, even though China has developed into the world's largest
steel producer, it is still far from being a steel power,
according to Wang Wanbin, the former director of the State
Metallurgical Industry Administration.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990822.0090 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-22 13:46 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 11 Kurdish Rebels Killed in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- A total of 11 rebels of the
outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) have been killed in recent
military operations in southeastern Turkey, an official statement
said on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The statement, issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule, said that the Turkish security forces had wiped out seven
PKK rebels in armed clashes in Zori region in Batman province,
two in Tunceli province and two in the provinces of Diyarbakir
and Sirnak.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the security forces captured four PKK militants in
the provinces of Diyarbakir and Sirnak and two PKK guerrillas
surrendered to the security forces in Bingol province.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting since 1984 a war for an independent
Kurdish state in southeastern Turkey, which has claimed over
37,000 lives in conflicts between the security forces and the
PKK. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990822.0091 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Industrial Competitiveness Increasing (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China remains an agricultural country, but, taking its current
economic scale and speed of development into account, analysts say
that it will grow into a modern industrialized country in the near
future.
</P>
<P>
Now in the country, large enterprises have begun to appear,
earning increasing international credibility. There are more than
1,600 enterprise groups above the provincial level that compete in
world markets and lead China in industrial development.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 50 years, the average growth rate of the
industrial sector was 13.6 percent, with the added value of
industrial output rising from less than 12 billion yuan in 1952 to
over 3.3 trillion yuan last year, and the number of employees
increasing 11 folds to 139 million and the number of enterprises
increasing 47 folds to about eight million, the NBS says.
</P>
<P>
The industrial sector has been contributing more to the country
's gross domestic product, which was 42.2 percent last year, and
remained to be the biggest single contributor to state revenues.
</P>
<P>
Market-oriented reform policies, a modern enterprise system,
and management expertise overseas have all breathed new vitality
into the country's industries, which have had new development
opportunities.
</P>
<P>
Fortunately for the industrial economy, China began to
encourage the development of overseas-funded and privately-run
industrial enterprises, which provided nearly 34 percent of the
country's total industrial output value in 1998, becoming a major
component of the national economy.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990822.0092 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Typhoon Sam Raids Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 22 (Xinhua) -- More than 100 people were
injured and some wooden shelters were destroyed as Typhoon Sam
raided Hong Kong on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The No. 8 northwest gale or storm signal was hoisted at 12:30
in Hong Kong, and the mean speed of winds reached 63 kilometers
per hour at noon in the northwest quarters.
</P>
<P>
At 1:00 p.m., Sam intensified into a typhoon and was centered
about 80 kilometers east-southeast of the Hong Kong Observatory
and moved northwest at about 18 kilometers per hour towards the
coast of Guangdong near Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Traffic was drastically reduced. Fishing boats and vessels were
not allowed to go out into the sea, few buses and pedestrians were
seen on the streets, and the airport was almost closed to flights.
</P>
<P>
Up to 3:00 p.m., a total of 24 incoming and outgoing flights
were delayed and six flights were canceled. Tram and ferry
services across the Victoria Harbor were suspended.
</P>
<P>
Two women and a man were injured this morning when a tree
collapsed and they were sent to a hospital for treatment.
</P>
<P>
The heavy rain also caused flooding in some areas.
</P>
<P>
Some stalls and shelters were devastated, and trees were
uprooted. A big fallen tree crashed into a running bus, but no one
was hurt.
</P>
<P>
Buses were also damaged with their headlights broken due to
traffic accidents caused by the heavy rain. Pedestrians feel
difficult in using their umbrellas and many broken umbrellas are
seen rolling on the streets.
</P>
<P>
Shops and stalls were closed to business. Schools and parks
were also closed and shelters were opened to those in difficulties.
A total of 352 people sought refuge at 33 temporary shelters
opened by the Home Affairs Department.
</P>
<P>
The strong winds blew at an average speed of over 130
kilometers.
</P>
<P>
At 9:00 p.m., the typhoon was centered about 35 kilometers
northwest of the Hong Kong and subsided gradually.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
