<HEADLINE> Austria Assists Tanzania in Developing Dairy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The Austrian government
has donated more than 125,000 U.S. dollars to help Tanzania
develop dairy industry.
</P>
<P>
The money will be used to fund activities like the review of
diary policies or laws, formulation of national dairy master plan,
sensitization of various stakeholders, and co-ordination of the
task force activities, Sunday News reported.
</P>
<P>
The activities will lead to the establishment of a national
platform for stakeholders in the dairy industry, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The money has been channeled to the task force of the National
Dairy Development Conference of Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
The leader of the task force, Prof. Lusato Kurwijila, said here
Saturday that the funds will be administered by Austro-project, a
non-governmental organization that has dairy products in Dar es
Salaam, Coast, Mara, and Arusha regions in Tanzania. 
</P>
</TEXT>
