<HEADLINE> China Adhering To Policy Of Revitalizing Through Science And Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Vice-premier Li Lanqing has said
that China will stick to its strategy of revitalizing the country
through science and education to bring a prosperous and socialist
China into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The remark came this weekend at an international seminar on
revitalizing the country through science and education, where Li
spoke about China's achievements in developing science and
technology and education since it decided on the strategy in 1995
at a national conference.
</P>
<P>
He said that in developing science and technology China should
stand on its own two feet while borrowing experiences from abroad
and he promised that the government will study the suggestions and
advice made by scholars attending the seminar. 
