<HEADLINE> Senior Afghan Taliban Official to Visit Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Afghan Taliban official for
foreign affairs Mohammad Hassan Akhund will make a four-day visit
to Pakistan starting next Tuesday for talks on a number of issues,
focusing on Afghan transit trade.
</P>
<P>
Hassan will lead a high-level delegation and will hold talks
with Pakistani Foreign Minister Sartaj Aziz to discuss bilateral
issues, especially controversy over the transit trade agreement,
official sources said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan imposed restrictions on Afghan transit trade a couple
of years ago, arguing that most of the goods imported under the
agreement are smuggled into Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Smuggling of the goods has affected Pakistan's local industry,
the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban authorities has repeatedly asked Pakistan to lift
the restrictions on transit trade.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that Islamabad's latest diplomatic efforts for
the peaceful settlement of the long-running Afghan crisis will
also come under discussion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
