<DOCNO> XIE19990822.0113 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-22 11:14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arafat in Egypt for talks with Mubarak, Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat
arrived in Egypt's Mediterranean port city of Alexandria on Sunday
for talks with President Hosni Mubarak and for a meeting later in
the day with the leader of an opposition Palestinian faction.
</P>
<P>
Arafat, accompanied by the planning minister and an advisor,
was greeted by Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa upon arrival
at the Bourg al Arab Airport, Egypt's Middle East News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
He is expected to discuss with Mubarak the talks between the
Palestinians and Israel on the timetable for the last two of the
three-phased further pullback of Israeli troops from the West Bank
under the Wye River peace agreement signed last October.
</P>
<P>
Following the meeting, Arafat, a frequent visitor to Egypt for
consultations with Mubarak on the Mideast peace process, will fly
to Cairo for a meeting with Nayef Hawatmah, secretary general of
the Democratic Front for the Liberation of Palestine (DFLP), the
news agency said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will be the first between Arafat and Hawatmah, who
arrived in Cairo on Saturday, since the 1993 signing of the Oslo
Accord, the main basis of the Palestinian-Israeli peace talks.
</P>
<P>
The upcoming meeting is part of Arafat's efforts to mend the
fences among Palestinian factions and try to reach a national
reconciliation and a united Palestinian position on the coming
final status talks on thorny and significant issues, including
Jerusalem and the Palestinian statehood, with Israel.
</P>
<P>
In an earlier step on August 1, Arafat met with a delegation of
another Palestinian opposition group - the People's Front for the
Liberation of Palestine (PFLP) - in Cairo. The two sides agreed to
continue dialog and called on other groups to join the process.
</P>
<P>
DFLP and PFLP, both based in the Syrian capital of Damascus,
are opposed to the Oslo Accord. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
