<HEADLINE> Kuwaiti Leaders Condole With Saudi King on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Kuwaiti leaders Sunday
extended condolences to Saudi King Fahd Ibn Abdul-Aziz on the
death of his eldest son Prince Faisal Ibn Fahd, who died of a
heart attack on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
In separate messages to King Fahd, Kuwaiti Emir Jaber Al-Ahmad
Al-Sabah, and Crown Prince and Prime Minister Saad Al-Abdullah
Al-Salem Al-Sabah "prayed to Almighty God to bless the soul of
Prince Faisal," head of the Saudi General Authority for Youth Care
and Sports, the Kuwait News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Emir Jaber has sent his advisor Sheikh Jaber Mubarak
Al-Hamad Al-Sabah to Riyadh representing him and the Kuwaiti
people to mourn the Saudi prince, who was also Chairman of the
Arab Confederation of Sporting Games.
</P>
<P>
Prince Faisal, 54, was not in the line to the throne, his
uncle, Crown Prince Abdullah Ibn Abdul-Aziz is the heir. 
</P>
