<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Troops Take Dagestan Rebels' Key Village, Supply Route </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Russian troops fighting Chechen
infiltrators in Daghestan captured the key village of Tando and an
important rebel supply route overnight, the Defense Ministry said
on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"We took over Tando and the Kharami mountain pass," a ministry
spokesman told reporters, adding that the pass was the main route
by which the rebels brought armor into Daghestan from Chechnya.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said Russian troops were continuing artillery
strikes on two other key villages, Ansalta and Rakhata, but no
infantry attack was under way.
</P>
<P>
He revealed that one Russian officer died in action on Saturday,
while 28 guerrillas were killed and one captured in the attack on
the mountain pass. During the fighting several vehicles were
destroyed and 17 anti-tank rocket launchers recovered.
</P>
<P>
Tando, which is located near the town of Botlikh in Dagestan's
southern mountains, has been the scene of much of the fiercest
fighting between Russian troops and the muslim guerrillas since
clashes began two weeks ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
