<HEADLINE> Italy Beats South Korea in Women Volleyball GP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Italy beat South Korea in five
sets on Sunday afternoon in Manila leg of the seventh one-million-
U.S.-dollar World Women's Volleyball Grand Prix.
</P>
<P>
The scores of the 5 sets are 13-25, 22-25, 26-24, 25-14 and 15-
10. The victory ranked Italy to the 3rd place of the GP's Manila
leg and South Korea was placed at 4th.
</P>
<P>
It was the first victory Italy made in the Manila leg. On
Friday and Saturday, Italy was beaten by Brazil and Cuba,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The last game of the GP's Manila leg is still ongoing between
Cuba and Brazil at press time. 
</P>
