<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: High Technology Industry Flourishing in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- China began to launch the "Torch
Program" for the commercial and industrial use of scientific
developments and the promotion of high technology industry in
August of 1988. The program has helped increase the proportion of
high technology remarkably in the whole national industry.
</P>
<P>
The key technological development fields for the program
include new materials, biological technology, electronics and
information, the combination of mechanics and electronics, new
energy and environment protection, and other high technology
fields.
</P>
<P>
The "Torch Program" has effectively promoted the development of
China's high technology industry during the past 11 years. In 1998,
projects of the "Torch Program" turned out a total of 144.5
billion yuan (about 17.4 billion US dollars) in output value and
26.6 billion yuan (about 4.2 billion US dollars) in revenue, and
earned 2.4 billion US dollars from exports.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, the program has established more than
12,000 projects, and developed a large group of hi-tech products
which include the New Era high-performance computer, type-04, type-
08 and SP-30 large and middle-sized program-controlled exchange
machines and other products.
</P>
<P>
The program also brought some large scientific group into
existence such as Founder, Legend and Stone, which have more than
one billion yuan of total assets and can turn out more than 100
million yuan in revenue each year.
</P>
<P>
To better implement the "Torch Program" and promote the
development of hi-tech industry, China has approved the
establishment of 53 national hi-tech industry development zones
across the country and granted them with favorable policies.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1998, those hi-tech development zones have
reported more than 480 billion yuan in their total income, and
produced 430 billion yuan in the total industrial output value,
both of which are much higher than the end of the previous year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
