<HEADLINE> Senegal Claims Final Berth in African Cup Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Senegal claimed the 16th and
final place in the African Cup of Nations on Saturday after
defeating Eritrea 2-0 in Asmara, Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
Henry Kamara gave Senegal the lead in the 46th minute and
Traore Mambara added the another goal in the final minute.
</P>
<P>
The victory gave Senegal a 3-0-1 record and nine points in the
three-nation playoff group, same as Zimbabwe but ahead on goal
difference.
</P>
<P>
The three-nation playoff was created after the African Football
Confederation (CAF) rescinded its decision to have Zimbabwe host
the finals in February, saying the country was unprepaped to stage
the biennial continental championship.
</P>
<P>
Ghana and Nigeria were selected to replace Zimbabwe in March.
</P>
<P>
The victory qualified Senegal for its sixth African Cup finals
and first since 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
