<HEADLINE> Postal Exhibition Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The five-day "'99 Postal China"
opened here today.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, as a coordinating event for the upcoming 22nd
Congress of the Universal Postal Union (UPU), is sponsored by the
State Post Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition attracted nearly 100 firms from 13 countries and
regions, including some world-known postal and telecommunications
operators, such as JVC, NEC and Siemens.
</P>
<P>
In the exhibition hall featuring Chinese firms, China Post,
China Unicom and other companies displayed their technology and
products, showing a rapid development of the country's postal
industry.
</P>
<P>
Equipment on show includes new business items developed with
new technology, equipment handling mail and information, and
vehicles for postal use.  
</P>
</TEXT>
