<HEADLINE> Souvenirs Mark Operation of New Subway in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- A total of 70,000 sets of items
for collection to mark the operation of the new subway section
from Fuxingmen to Bawangfen in Beijing on September 28 will be
available at different postal bureaus of the Chinese capital from
September 8.
</P>
<P>
Each set consists of two commemorative magnetic cards, and a
special commemorative envelope and will be sold at a price of 120
yuan.
</P>
<P>
Both the magnetic cards and the envelope are the first of their
kinds in Beijing. Holders of the magnetic cards can also get 30
free tickets for sight-seeing along the Fuxingmen-Bawangfen new
subway section at automats installed at subway stations.
</P>
<P>
The items for collection, jointly made by Beijing Subway
Economic, Technological Trading Corporation and another Beijing-
based company, will be jointly issued by Beijing Subway
Corporation and Beijing Municipal Postal Bureau.  
</P>
</TEXT>
