<HEADLINE> Malawian Cable Thieves Troubles President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Malawian cable thieves have cut
off President Bakili Muluzi's telephone line and made the
president out of touch with home while he was away in Mozambique
for a regional summit.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on his return, the president warned the thieves that
they are in big trouble if they are caught, according to reports
reaching here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The country's phone company has offered a reward for the arrest
of the thieves.
</P>
<P>
Malawi, with 11 million people, is one of the world's poorest
countries with an average annual per capital income of about 200
U.S. dollars a year.
</P>
<P>
Telephone cables have been one of the major targets of the
thieves in the southern African country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
