<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Strong Winds Cause Damages in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The strong winds sweeping into
Hong Kong today have caused some damages to the properties and
local people.
</P>
<P>
Some stalls and shelters have been devastated, trees are
uprooted and many roads are closed.
</P>
<P>
Some buses are also damaged with their headlights broken due to
accidents. Pedestrians feel difficult in using their umbrellas and
many broken umbrellas are seen rolling on the streets.
</P>
<P>
Shops and stalls are closed to business. Schools are closed and
shelters are opened to those in difficulties.
</P>
<P>
The strong winds, including Signal NO.8 and NO.3, are blowing
at an average speed of over 130 kilometers. And strong tropical
wind Sam is soon to embark on Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
At 10 a.m., the center of severe tropical storm Sam was
estimated to be about 130 kilometers east-southeast of Hong Kong
and is forecast to move northwest at about 16 kilometers per hour
towards the coast of Guangdong near Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
At 1 p.m., Sam had intensified into a typhoon and was centered
about 80 kilometers east-southeast of the Hong Kong Observatory.
It is forecast to move northwest at about 16 kilometers per hour
towards the coast of Guangdong near Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Sam will be closest to Hong Kong very soon.
</P>
<P>
All traffics have been drastically reduced. Fishing boats and
vessels are not allowed to go out into the sea, airport is almost
closed to flights, few buses and pedestrians are seen on the
streets and the public is being alerted.
</P>
<P>
The public is reminded to be on the alert and take all
necessary preparations to protect themselves. 
</P>
</TEXT>
