<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin to Start Peace and Friendship Tour to Bishkek (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin will begin
a trip to Bishkek, capital of Kyrgyzstan, between August 24 and 26
for a five-nation summit meeting among China, Russia, Kazakhstan,
Kyrgyzstan and Tajikistan, at the invitation of Kyrgyzstan's
President Askar Akayev.
</P>
<P>
The heads of state of the five countries will discuss and
exchange views on international situation, regional security and
economic cooperation, officials with the Foreign Ministry told
Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
"The tour will be one of peace and friendship," said an
official of the ministry.
</P>
<P>
The Bishkek summit will be the fourth for the leaders. During
the previous meetings, they signed two agreements on building
confidence in the military area and on mutual reduction of armed
forces in border areas, and the Alma-Ata Joint Statement.
</P>
<P>
Observers here said that those documents have helped strengthen
mutual trust and cooperation between the five countries, and have
also created a new type of security concept totally different from
the cold war mentality.
</P>
<P>
In addition, they say that the meetings have helped the
formation of a new method in increasing mutual understanding and
trust among nations.
</P>
<P>
"The five-nation summit has already played and will continue to
play an important role in maintaining peace and stability in the
Eurasia region, and in promoting regional economic cooperation,"
said an analyst here.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
