<DOCNO> XIE19990822.0147 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin to Start Peace and Friendship Tour to Bishkek (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The upcoming summit in Bishkek at the turn of the century will
be another important event that will serve as a link between the
past and the future, analysts say.
</P>
<P>
Great changes have taken place since the beginning of the year,
and world peace is faced with severe challenge. The negative side
of economic globalization is also showing up.
</P>
<P>
Under those circumstances, the five countries all wish to
expand and enrich their cooperation for the sake of safeguarding
regional security and stability as well as promoting economic
growth, the foreign ministry official pointed out.
</P>
<P>
That will also be one of the major topics of the current summit
meeting, he said.
</P>
<P>
During the upcoming summit, President Jiang is expected to
discuss with leaders of the other four countries on new ways of
cooperation for regional security and economic prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Relevant departments of the five nations will establish a multi-
level mechanism of dialog, consultation and cooperation, and will
also make concerted efforts to continue their fights against
forces that threaten regional security such as international
terrorism and national separatism, according to the official.
</P>
<P>
In addition, officials told Xinhua that during the summit
meeting, Jiang will sign an additional border document with
Kyrgyzstan's President Askar Akayev.
</P>
</TEXT>
