but said he was not able to divulge "changes in the delivery
timetable" or details of which purchases could end up being
indefinitely shelved.
</P>
<P>
He said negotiations with all suppliers had been concluded and
that, " in the end, it is Manuel who will decide".
</P>
<P>
Naidoo was speaking as a furore erupted over an anonymous
report distributed in Parliament this week claimed that six
billion rand (1 billion dollars) would be wasted if the navy went
ahead with its plan to buy new ships and submarines.
</P>
<P>
It stated that the "procurement process for the South African
navy surface vessels has gone astray".
</P>
