<HEADLINE> Stamp Collection Popular in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The stamps business has
developed fast in China over the past five decades, thanks to the
world's largest group of stamps collectors in the world's most
populous country.
</P>
<P>
According to the State Postal Bureau (SPB), China now has more
than 20 million stamps collectors. In 1998, SPB earned 7.8 billion
yuan through stamps collection business, accounting for over 14
percent of its total revenue. Stamps issuance has become one of
the three pillar business areas of SPB.
</P>
<P>
Since new China issued its first stamps in 1949, it will have
issued 3,209 stamps in 812 issuances and 805 post cards in 147
issuances by October 1, this year. It has also issued many pre-
stamped envelops and other postage carriers.
</P>
<P>
It has jointly issued ten sets of stamps with 13 countries,
including the United States, France, Canada, Sweden, Switzerland,
Singapore and Thailand.
</P>
<P>
China now has three printing houses to print stamps for itself.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
