<DOCNO> XIE19990822.0165 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Maldives to Hold Parliament Election in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The Maldives is to elect a new
unicameral parliament in November for the next five years, said
reports reaching here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Maldivians over 21 years old will elect 40 members of Majlis,
or People's Council, said the reports, adding that the president
will appoint the other eight members of the council.
</P>
<P>
The election will be monitored by observers from various South
Asian nations, the reports added.
</P>
<P>
The Maldives is an archipelago of more than 1,200 low-lying
coral islands spreading across the equator in the Indian Ocean. It
has a population of 260,000 people with tourism, fishing and
shipping as its main business.
</P>
<P>
The Muslim nation has no political parties and individuals bid
for parliament as independent candidates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
