<DOCNO> XIE19990822.0166 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Perkins Suffers Another Confidence Sapper </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Kieren Perkins' triple Olympic
1500m freestyle hopes took another setback Sunday when he
struggled to 14th in the 400m heats on the opening day of the Pan
Pacific Swimming Championship in Sydney.
</P>
<P>
The 26-year-old Australian dual Olympic champion appeared to be
suffering the effects of a virus as he jumped in for his first
race of the championships in the Olympic pool.
</P>
<P>
Perkins laboured home in three minutes 59.27 seconds, almost 12
seconds slower than his teammate Grant Hackett, the fastest
qualifier in 3:47.37.
</P>
<P>
Perkins' time was also more than 15 seconds slower than his
1994 world record (3:43.80) at the Rome World Championships.
</P>
<P>
Australian coach Denis Cotterell said the virus had stripped
the triple world record-holder of three kilograms in weight.
</P>
<P>
Perkins wants to become the first male swimmer to win gold
medals in the same event at three successive Olympics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
