<HEADLINE> Tsyzyu Claims WBC Super Lightweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Australian Kostya Tszyu
stopped former champion Miguel Angel Gonzalez of Mexico 48 seconds
into the 10th round in Houston Friday night to claim the WBC super
lightweight title.
</P>
<P>
Tszyu dominated the action so much the Mexican's corner called
for the end of the bout.
</P>
<P>
Tszyu improved to 23-1-1 with his 19th win while Gonzalez fell
to 43-2-1. 
