<DOCNO> XIE19990822.0177 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Exports from Bangladesh's Exporting Processing Zones Up by 12 Pct </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Exports from Bangladesh's two
export processing zones (EPZs) increased by about 12 percent in
the 1998-99 fiscal year ending on June 30 as compared to that in
the previous fiscal year, The Financial Express daily newspaper
reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Industries in the Chittagong Export Processing Zone (CEPZ) and
the Dhaka Export Processing Zone (DEPZ) earned an amount of 711.69
million U.S. dollars in the 1998-99 fiscal year by exporting their
products as against their exports worth 636.04 million dollars in
the 1997-98 fiscal year, sources were quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Of the total amount, the CEPZ exported goods worth about 452.12
million dollars while the DEPZ exported goods worth about 295.57
million dollars.
</P>
<P>
With the present exports, the two EPZs' cumulative export
earnings stood at 2.865 billion dollars, of which, the CEPZ had
exported goods worth about 2.18 billion dollars while that of the
DEPZ stood at 684 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The products exported from the two EPZs included garments,
textiles, metal products, plastic goods, footwear, leather
products, sports goods, paper, knitting and other textile
products.
</P>
<P>
A total of 391.68 million dollars has been so far invested in
the CEPZ while 123.69 million dollars invested in the DEPZ. Among
the investors, South Korea accounted for the major investment of
about 144.69 million dollars followed by Japan and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The garments and textile sector accounted for the major
investment of about 97.71 million dollars, followed by leather,
sports, knitting, metal products and other garment accessories.
</P>
<P>
Till now, 148 industries have been set up in the two EPZs, and
of the industries, 78 industrial units belong to "A" category, 33
to "B" category and the rest 37 belong to "C" category. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
