<HEADLINE> Bolivia Determined to Combat Drug Trafficking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Bolivian President Hugo Banzer said
Saturday that his government will combat drug trafficking in his
country.
</P>
<P>
Bolivia is changing from a nation that produces drugs to one
that combats drug trafficking, said Banzer during a ceremony in
the city of Sucre, 740 kilometers south of La Paz, according to a
report reaching here from the Bolivian capital.
</P>
<P>
Banzer said that 24,000 hectares of illegal coca cultivation
have been eliminated by his government in the last two years in
the Bolivian province of El Chapare, and the government will
continue to combat corruption and drug trafficking with juridical
means.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that head of U.S. anti-drug office Barry
McCaffrey will visit Bolivia next Tuesday and Wednesday. 
</P>
