<HEADLINE> Mexico Seizes 535 Kg of Marihuana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Mexican Federal Attorney
Office (PGR) agents seized 535 kilograms of marihuana in
operations Saturday in the states of Sonora and Baja California
and detained six persons.
</P>
<P>
The PGR said that three vehicles, firearms and ammunition were
confiscated in the operations.
</P>
<P>
In the first action made in a dirt landing strip near Magdalena
de Kino, Sonora, anti-drug police and troops seized 300 kilograms
of marihuana in 69 packages from a light plane and a pickup truck
with a Sonora license plate.
</P>
<P>
In another action, PGR agents found 200 kilograms of marihuana
in Tijuana, Baja California, and detained two people on the
Colorado-Mexicali road.  
