<HEADLINE> People's Daily Hails Opening of Postal Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- "People's Daily", China's
leading newspaper, carries an editorial today, expounding that the
staging of the 22nd Congress of the Universal Postal Union (UPU)
tomorrow in Beijing is very significant for both China and the
world.
</P>
<P>
This will be a great event in China's relations with the
outside world, as well as in its reform and opening-up process,
according to the editorial, titled "An Opening China Is Pleased to
Welcome Guests from Postal Services Throughout the World".
</P>
<P>
It says that the event is a part of China's multilateral
diplomatic strategy, and President Jiang Zemin has taken the
position of the honorary chairman of the organizing committee,
because the gathering is so important.
</P>
<P>
Now the country is fully ready for the grand opening, as a good
environment has been created by more than 20 ministries and
commissions and other institutions over the past years, according
to the article.
</P>
<P>
It continues that the congress will be a window for the nation
to show its achievements in the past 50 years, particularly, the
past 20 years, during which the reform and opening-up were on full
swing.
</P>
<P>
The article says that China has had postal services for 3,000
years, and since new China was founded, the Chinese Government has
taken a lot of measures to modernize the sector, which is
important in guaranteeing the right to communications, a major
part of the human rights.
</P>
<P>
"China has established the largest postal system in the world,"
the paper says, adding that it is doing something to upgrade the
technologies.
</P>
<P>
The editorial stresses that the congress will help step up the
reform and development of China's postal sector, which is being
driven by the market force and faced with huge social demands.
</P>
<P>
It says that China has established postal links with 145
countries and regions, and the opening of the congress will enable
the country to open wider to the outside world.
</P>
<P>
The congress is the last one the UPU to stage in the century,
so it is significant for bringing the world into a promising
future, and the development strategy formulated by the congress
will have a great impact on the political and economic interest of
different countries, the editorial says.  
</P>
</TEXT>
