<HEADLINE> Tottenham Win to Top Premier League Table </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Tottenham Hotspur moved into the
top spot in England for the first time in 13 years after beating
Sheffield Wednesday 2-1 on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Their stay would prove to be short-lived when arch-rivals
Arsenal meet champions Manchester United at Highbury on Sunday and
whoever wins that game will leapfrog Spurs by a point.
</P>
<P>
If Arsenal and Manchester United draw then Spurs will remain in
pole position on goal difference from Middlesbrough.
</P>
<P>
Spurs victory, thanks to first half goals from Les Ferdinand
and Norwegian international Oyvind Leonhardsen, meant they have
won three successive league matches for the first time in four
years.
</P>
<P>
Middlesbrough beat Liverpool 1-0 with Brian Deane scoring the
only goal early in the second half.
</P>
<P>
With Spurs and Middlesbrough top on nine points, United slipped
back to third and are one of six teams on seven points along with
Chelsea, Aston Villa, Leeds United, West Ham and Arsenal. United,
Chelsea, West Ham and Arsenal all have a game in hand over the top
two.
</P>
<P>
Chelsea moved up from seventh to fourth with their 1-0 win over
Aston Villa at Stamford Bridge thanks to an own goal from Ugo
Ehiogu after 52 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The most dramatic game of the day was at St James' Park where
Newcastle, without the suspended England skipper Alan Shearer,
squandered a 3-1 lead and allowed Wimbledon to grab a 3-3 draw.
</P>
<P>
That result gave Newcastle their first point of the season
after three straight defeats and they remain 18th with only Derby
County and Sheffield Wednesday below them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
