<DOCNO> XIE19990822.0196 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Costa Rica Expects Strong Earthquakes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rican authorities expect
possible earthquakes of higher intensity than the one registered
last Friday, an official of National Emergency Commission (CNE)
said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Fernando Cordero told Xinhua by telephone that the earth
movements occurred in the last two days in the country. The
research of Costa Rican seismologists shows that it is highly
possible that in the Nicoya peninsula in the Pacific coast north
of Costa Rica there will be very strong earthquakes that could
cause much damage to the population.
</P>
<P>
The Costa Rican authorities have taken preventive measures to
reduce the damage, said the CNE official.
</P>
<P>
He also confirmed that an earthquake with a magnitude of 4.8 on
the Richter scale occurred at 04:49 Saturday and its epicenter was
located 55 kilometers southeast of Quepos, some 120 km south of
San Jose, at a depth of 35 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
This earth movement was caused by the collision of the Cocos
and Caribbean tectonic plates, the same as Friday's, that measured
5.3 on the Richter scale. None of the two tremors caused damage or
victims. 
</P>
</TEXT>
