<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Colombian Paramilitary Men Slay Five Villagers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- A group of armed men
shot dead five more villagers in northern Colombia Saturday,
bringing the total murdered in the week to at least 20, a police
source said.
</P>
<P>
Other three villagers were injured by firearms as they escaped
the armed men, who were searching the place for suspected members
or collaborators of the guerrillas, the source said without
mentioning the number of the attackers.
</P>
<P>
The villagers were forcibly taken from their homes and shot
dead right in front of the eyes of their relatives.
</P>
<P>
The police blamed the killings on paramilitary groups that
combat the guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
The Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC), the biggest
rebel group in the country, criticized the government's leniency
toward the paramilitary groups, which have made a series of
assassinations recently in the rural areas of the war-torn country.
</P>
</TEXT>
