<HEADLINE> Romanian Deputy PM Insists on One China Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Romanian Deputy Prime Minister
Victor Babiuc said Saturday Romania has persisted in the one China
policy over the past 50 years, adding that his country has not and
will not change this stand.
</P>
<P>
"There is only one China in the world and Taiwan is an
inalienable part of Chinese territory," Babiuc told a visiting
Chinese military delegation.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his belief that China has the patience and power
to deal with the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
"The Taiwan issue will be resolved someday and victory will
belong to Chinese people," said the deputy prime minister.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese military delegation, led by Wu Quanxu, deputy chief
of the general staff, arrived here Wednesday for a five-day visit.
</P>
