<HEADLINE> U.S. Anti-Drug Official to Visit Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The head of the U.S. Drug Control
National Policy Office will arrive here next Wednesday, as part of
his four-nation South American tour, the Peruvian Foreign
Ministry announced Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Barry McCaffrey, who will also visit Brazil, Bolivia and
Argentina, will meet Peruvian President Alberto Fujimori Thursday
on the progress of the anti-drug war in Peru, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
McCaffrey will also meet members of the Commission of the Fight
Against Drug Consuming.
</P>
<P>
McCaffrey will examine in his South American tour the
preparations for the Hemispheric Conference on Anti-drug Policy to
be held on November 3-5 in Washington.
</P>
<P>
Peru and the United States recently signed two anti-drug
cooperation agreements.
</P>
<P>
Peruvian authorities said that during the past five years the
Fujimori government reduced from 115,300 to 51,000 hectares the
area cultivated with coca plants, whose leaves are used to produce
cocaine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
