<DOCNO> XIE19990822.0204 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 3.5 Million Tremors Occur Every Year Worldwide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 3.5 million earthquakes
are registered every year in the world and at least one of them
surpasses the magnitude of 8 on the Richter scale, Spain's
National Seismic Network reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
It said that almost 1,000 tremors of a magnitude above 5 are
reported in the world, of which 18 are between 7 and 7.9, 120
between 6 and 6.9, and 800 between 5 and 5.8.
</P>
<P>
The Seismic Network said that it must be considered that the
epicenter of many of them can be in the middle of the sea or of
the desert, so they do not directly affect the population and go
unnoticed.
</P>
<P>
The zones of the biggest risk are in the areas where the
tectonic plates meet each other, meaning between America and the
Pacific, in Japan or in the Mediterranean zone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
