<HEADLINE> Three Top Seeds into Canadian Open Semis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Three top seeds--Martina Hingis
of Switzerland, American Monica Seles and Mary Pierce of France--
all advanced into the semi-finals of the Canadian Open in Toronto
on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The fourth semi-finalist was unseeded Anne-Gaelle Sidot of
France, who upset sixth seed Amanda Coetzer of South Africa 5-7, 6-
4, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Hingis downed fifth-seeded Arantxa Sanchez Vicario of Spain 6-1,
6-1, Seles overcame ninth-seeded Barbara Schett of Austria 6-3, 3-
6, 6-1 and Pierce needed only three games to finish the resumption
of Friday's match with her countrywoman Sandrine Testud, winning 6-
1, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
The semifinal line-up later on Saturday will be Seles meeting
Sidot and Hingis taking on Pierce. 
</P>
</TEXT>
