<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Factfile on World Men's Shot Put Champion Hunter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEVILLE, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Following is the factfile on C.J.
Hunter who won the men's shot put title on the opening day of the
world championships on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Born: December 14, 1968.
</P>
<P>
First name is Cottrell but prefers to be known by his initials.
</P>
<P>
First in the 1994 World Cup, second in the 1995 world indoor
championships and third in the 1997 Athens world outdoor
championships.
</P>
<P>
Throwing coach at the University of North Carolina and husband
of sprinter and long jumper Marion Jones. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
