<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Factfile on World 20kms Walk Champion Markov </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEVILLE, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Following is the factfile on
Ilya Markov of Russia who won the world men's 20 kms walk on the
opening day of the world championships on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Born: June 19, 1972
</P>
<P>
First over 10 kms at the 1990 world junior championships,
graduated to the senior ranks and finished fourth in the 1995
Gothenburg world championships before taking silver in the 1996
Atlanta Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Third in the 1997 World Cup after being disqualified in the
Athens world championships of the same year.
</P>
<P>
Set world indoor mile best of five minutes 31.8 seconds this
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
