<DOCNO> XIE19990822.0217 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 3 Shot to Death in New Riot in Ambon, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- At least three people were
killed and eight others were injured in a new riot in Ambon,
capital of Indonesia's Maluku province, on Saturday afternoon, the
Antara News Agency reported on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The incident started when large numbers of unidentified people
arrived near a market on Tulukabessy Street in Kijang vans and
trucks.
</P>
<P>
The rioters attacked a shophouse complex and torched 10 of the
complex's units with self-made incendiary bombs and molotov
cocktails.
</P>
<P>
Two fire trucks belonging to the Ambon municipal administration
could not come close enough to the burning buildings to do their
job because rioters blocked their path even though they were
escorted by a security forces detail.
</P>
<P>
Most of the dead casualties were hit by bullets fired by
security forces, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The clashes in Ambon first broke out in January, in which more
than one hundred people were killed and tens of thousands of
people were forced to flee their villages.
</P>
<P>
Local religious figures, along with the military, have tried to
reconcile the warring camps but clashes broke out again in
mid-July.
</P>
<P>
In Ambon, about 60 percent of the population is Christian. Most
of the rest are Muslims, many of them immigrants from other
islands. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
