<HEADLINE> Spadea, Lapentti Contests RCA Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Two surprising finalists--
eleventh seed Nicolas Lapentti of Ecuador and unseeded American
Vince Spadea--will contest the title of the RCA Championships
which started with many star players.
</P>
<P>
The 34th-ranked Spadea reached his second career ATP Tour final
by outlasting 32nd-ranked Frenchman Sebastien Grosjean 6-3, 6-7 (4-
7), 7-6(7-4) in two hours, 44 minutes on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 23-year-old Lapentti scored a 6-4, 6-2 victory over Jan
Siemerink of the Netherlands in a brief 69 minutes.
</P>
<P>
All the star players had gone out earlier. Top-seeded Pete
Sampras exited midway through his quarter-final match against
Spadea with a right hip flexor strain. Second-seeded Patrick
Rafter never took to the court in his quarter-final against
Siemerink because of shoulder tendinitis.
</P>
<P>
Third-seeded Gustavo Kuerten of Brazil lost in straight sets to
Grosjean, and Lapentti overwhelmed fourth-seeded Carlos Moya of
Spain. 
</P>
