<DOCNO> XIE19990822.0239 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Markov Wins First Gold in Athletics Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEVILLE, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Russia's Ilya Markov captured
the first gold medal of the 7th World Athletics Championships by
winning the men's 20 kilometers walking here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Markov, who was disaqualified with five kilometers to go in the
Athens championships in 1997, pulled away from the leading pack in
the last last two kilometers and took the win comfortably in one
hour 23 minutes 34 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Olympic Champion Jefferson Perez of Ecuador finished second in
1:24:19 and defending champion Daniel Garcia of Mexico third in 1:
24:31.
</P>
<P>
Markov, the reigning European champion and silver medalist in
the 1996 Olympic Games, contributed his gold medal to his wife. "
Today is her birthday, this gold is for her, " he said.
</P>
<P>
"It's extremely hot, especially for a Russian but I'm in superb
form today. Before the competition, I know my top rival is Perez
because I lost to him in the 1996 Olympics. During walking, I'm
confident of winning the gold, " he said.
</P>
<P>
The Russian suffered a heartbreaking defeat in the 1997
championships where he held the lead most of the time but was
disqualified as the victory was in sight.
</P>
<P>
China's hope of winning a medal in the race was dashed as Li
Zewen, the 1995 World Cup champion, finished only fourth.
</P>
<P>
The world's most populous country, who failed to win a medal of
any color in Athens, now must fix their eyes on the women's 20km
walking for a medal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
